  "dataFlow": "1. TRIGGER: A build session originates from one of: (a) HTTP POST /api/build from the Next.js dashboard, (b) GitHub/Linear webhook POST /api/webhook verified by HMAC, (c) autonomy poller detecting a Linear Todo issue, or (d) cron trigger dispatched by cron.py. 2. SESSION CREATION: create_session() in sessions.py creates a BuildSession object (in-memory + atomic JSON to app/logs/sessions/{sid}.json), then asyncio.create_task(run_build(session)) launches the pipeline. 3. CLONE: The pipeline clones the target repo into app/workspaces/{sid}/ via git. 4. BRIEF CLASSIFICATION: PITER classifier determines intent (feature/bug/chore/spike/hotfix) and selects an ADW workflow template; relevant lessons from .harness/lessons.jsonl are injected into the system prompt. 5. GENERATION: _run_claude_via_sdk() constructs a ClaudeSDKClient with bypassPermissions mode, sends the enriched prompt, and streams assistant messages back into session.output_lines as structured events. 6. EVALUATION: The evaluator tier spawns a second SDK session, reads git diff HEAD~1, grades 4 dimensions (Completeness/Correctness/Conciseness/Format), compares to EVALUATOR_THRESHOLD; if below threshold up to TAO_EVALUATOR_MAX_RETRIES re-runs of generation are attempted with the critique injected. 7. STREAMING: As events arrive they are appended to session.output_lines and pushed to any connected WebSocket (/ws/build/{sid}) or polled by the SSE endpoint (/api/sessions/{sid}/logs). 8. PERSISTENCE: Every status change calls persistence.save_session() using write-to-.tmp-then-os.replace() for atomicity. 9. OBSERVABILITY: supabase_log.py fire-and-forgets gate_checks and alert_escalations rows to Supabase; agent-sdk-metrics/{date}.jsonl captures per-invocation cost/latency. 10. NOTIFICATIONS: On terminal state or critical findings, outbound Telegram messages are sent via urllib POST to api.telegram.org. 11. LINEAR SYNC: On session completion, a Linear issue state transition is called (issueUpdate mutation) — gap audit RA-665 flags this as partially unimplemented.",
